==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: parsimoniousness
<hw>parsimoniousness</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of
being parsimonious; extreme care in spending money; reluctance to spend
money unnecessarily.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> parsimony, thrift, penny-pinching.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An extreme stinginess.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> meanness, minginess, niggardliness, niggardness,
parsimony, tightfistedness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parsimony</ent>⟦br⟧
